        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Ancagalon</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> COS is one of those tools that comes in handy in so many situations, it might be hard to fully outline the impact it has. Some of them might be:</P><P>-Instantly kill a pet. Slightly less of a concern with the new pet changes, but still an important tool. A critter gets away from you/your group, and Jaboner is just out of your range to hear your /pet back off command. Circlet.<BR>-Stay invis every second that you are not actively casting a spell when you do not have a pet up. Helps with root-DOTing in crowded areas. Substantially less chance of agroing wanderers.<BR>-Pull through nasty areas. Run past a bunch of critters while invis. Target one, hit it with a spell. Hit your circlet and run back out, not having to pull the critters you ran past (subject to several agro rules, but effective in a lot of areas).<BR>-Get a FD off in the middle of a crowd of critters. Normally, you cannot stand up, or they will agro. But, stand and COS. Because the invis is instant, they will not agro (providing your FD wiped the hate list).<BR>-Invis without needing mana.<BR>-Invis without having to have it memorized.<BR>-If you are an exceptionally annoying player, stand beside someone in a laggy zone and hammer on your circlet hotkey, which an often cause them to go LD. <BR>-In a duel, if you go invis and the other player does not have a see-invis effect on, they lose you as a target. Almost guanteed way to win a duel (it ain't pretty, but if the win is what you are after, what the hell). <BR>-There is one other big strategy that is probably considered exploitive, so I will not include it here.</P><P>There are lots more. One of those things that is very flexible, and of all the items I have ever owned, or ever plan on owning, it is easily the one that has saved my boney ass more times then every single other item I have put together. It is the item that is clicked most often. It is the item I miss the most when I play any of my alts. It is the item that there is not enough plat in the game today to make me give up.</P><P>Cheers,<BR>Ancagalon the Black<BR>Warlock - Terris Thule</P><P> </font></td>
