        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Kuotat</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> What makes a Circlet of Shadow so invaluable?  Instant cast invisibility.  Because it's insta-cast you don't have to be standing still nor is there a delay that's normally associated with casting invis. </P><P>Tactics explained that have been mentioned that you can't do w/o one.</P><P>FD-Getup.  FD in front of a bunch of MOB's or a stationary MOB (that FD makes you drop agro from).  Normally you can't do anything except wait for FD to refresh run some more and FD again.  With a Circlet, if your clicks/finger/macro is fast enough you can get up and invis right in front of the MOB with no agro.</P><P>Invis Pulling - Normally you agro a MOB you run by his buddies and you then have the beginnings of a great agro train.  With a circlet, you agro the MOB and start running to where ever you want.  Because it's insta-click invis, you click invis on the run and do NOT agro anything that doesn't see thru invis.  If your invis drops for some reason, click it again.</P><P>Exploring - There is no delay in a cast time associated with the Circlet, so you can stand right in front of Ready To Attack MOB_01 and click your circlet all day.  They won't agro.</P><P>Poofing Pet - Handy, but probably not as big a deal anymore.  Slim get's a mind of his own.  Click...instant Slim Perm-Time-Out.</P><P>It doesn't allow you to do anything you can't do invis, but it does allow you to do many things much better.  These are only some of the uses, it's a must have for any Necro or SK.</P><P></P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=95266" target="_blank">Kuotat Smith</a><BR><s>Warlock</s> Witch<BR>Mithaniel Marr</font></td>
